OL,7,FThe group of ministers "dispensed with
OL,8,Fthe need for a full business case
OL,9,Fbefore approving the acquisition",
OL,10,Faccording to the NAO's findings.
OL,12,FThe watchdog's report concluded: "The
OL,13,FHome Office's attempt to acquire the
OL,14,FNortheye site within just a few
OL,15,Fmonths... led it to cut corners and
OL,16,Fmake a series of poor decisions.
OL,18,F"This resulted in it purchasing a site
OL,19,Fthat was unsuitable for that original
OL,20,Fpurpose and it paying more for it than
OL,21,Fit needed to."
